Introductory article about the university:

Known as “Polytech”, Irkutsk National Research Technical University is a center of science, culture, and education in the Irkutsk Region. INRTU challenges students to excel in the fields of nanotechnology, aircraft and mechanical engineering, energy, mining, oil and gas, chemical technology, construction and architecture, examine ecology and environmental engineering in the area with the advantageous location next to the lake Baikal, the deepest lake on the Earth, the biggest reservoir of fresh water on the continent.

Recognizing the importance of Baikal for the Irkutsk Region and the entire planet, INRTU perceives the importance of saving Baikal and its unique nature with endemic species of fish and animals and rare plants in a state of nature for future generations and protecting the lake from harmful human influence. For these reason, INRTU is committed on establishing effective educational programs and doing research in the field of ecology and green engineering.

INRTU aims to offer the best possible education. The University cultivates breadth and depth in the skills, knowledge, and capacities that help students flourish in whatever future emerges. An integral part of the educational process and research activities in INRTU are numerous field trips and expeditions, scientific and practical seminars, conferences and symposiums thank to which students have the opportunity not only to learn from eminent scientists, but also to give a good account of themselves in a scientific field under the supervision of experienced professors. All this undoubtedly makes INRTU attractive not only to residents of the Irkutsk Region and adjoining regions of Russia, but also to students from other countries.

Facts

INRTU conducts research in 24 of the 69 fields of expertise contained in State Classifier of Scientific and Technical Information, and covers 6 of the 9 priority areas of the development of science, technics and technology in the Russian Federation.
INRTU Technopark is home to research labs, training, production, and corporate research centers, a business-incubator and a spacious conference hall.
Our university interacts with international partners from 21 countries in scientific and educational fields
INRTU conducts active academic cooperation and joint cooperation in double diploma programs with partners from Asia and Europe: Republic of Korea, Czech Republic, Finland, France, Germany, China, Poland.
INRTU became a part of 8 technological platforms created in the Russian Federation.
INRTU is a member of international associations, networks, organizations

International Accreditation

European Network for Accreditation
 of Engineering Education (ENAEE)

European Network for Accreditation of Engineering Education is an international network of national accreditation and quality assurance agencies working in accordance with approved standards to accredit engineering programs. Russian Federation is presented by Association for Engineering Education of Russian , which is one of ENAEE founders.

Accreditation agencies, ENAEE members have the right to award the  EUR-ACE®  (EURopean ACcredited Engineer) label to accredited engineering degree programmes and register these programs in international list of ENAEE and  FEANI (Fédération Européenne d’Associations Nationales d’Ingénieurs).

International accreditation and EUR-ACE® label provide the following advantages:

Independent evaluation of program quality of by international experts;
Recommendations on educational program improvement;
Registration of an educational program in the All-European  list of accredited engineering programs
Increase of competitiveness at international and national markets of educational services;
Providing more job placement opportunities for educational program graduates;
Chance to obtain professional title EUR ING for graduates of an educational program.
Acknowledgement of the high quality of an educational program on the All-European level;

University were Accredited by ENAEE

2015: 4 master degree programs of the University were accredited by ENAEE for 5 years (2015-2020) and awarded with the label EUR-ACE® Master:
  • Technology, Equipment and Quality System for Welding
  • Food Engineering
  • Population Saving, Occupational, Environmental and Disaster Risk Management
  • Fire Protection
